    • getImportSampleIDData

      public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Object> getImportSampleIDData(org.springframework.web.multipart.MultipartHttpServletRequest request, com.agaramtech.qualis.global.UserInfo userInfo) throws Exception
      This method is used to retrieve sample storage details based on imported excel. Here the imported excel sheet is iterated to get the sampleIDs as String ("filterquery") with conditions added to it and is put into inputMap [Map] map with keys "source","label","valuemember","nprojecttypecode" and "filterquery". This inputMap and userInfo is then sent to getDynamicFilterExecuteData() in the same DAOImpl class to get the stored sample details.
      Specified by:
      getImportSampleIDData in interface SampleStorageListPreperationDAO
      Parameters:
      request - [MultipartHttpServletRequest] multipart request with parameters: ImportFile,nformcode,userinfo,nprojecttypecode,source,fieldName,label,valuemember
      userInfo - [UserInfo] holding logged in user details and nmasterSiteCode [int] primary key of site object for which the list is to be fetched
      Returns:
      response object with list of sample storage details based on imported excel.
      Throws:
      Exception - that are thrown in the DAO layer
